  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "The Economic Reform Technical Assistance Project for Nepal aims to support the implementation of key short term measures of the reform agenda as embodied in the Royal Proclamation, the 21-point program, and the PRS. The Nepal Economic Reform Technical Assistance Project (NERTA) should be structured to provide flexibility in sourcing and building capacity. During the preparation and appraisal meetings, Bank support was requested in the following areas; (i) improving governance and public sector management; (ii) accelerating privatization; (iii) improving service delivery; and (iv) implementing a strategic communications program. A brief overview of support in each of these areas is presented below. It is proposed that these areas form the areas of pre-identified technical assistance while the remainder of the resources is placed in a challenge fund."
    },
    "ne": null
  },
